through this journey and neither compares to the feeling of riding away from a trick that you‚Äôve battled for hours, weeks or years. I continue to do it because I can still be creative in a way gives me a personal sense of pride and validation.

both physically and emotionally, for being singularly focused on something. I hope that it gives some perspective on why we do this and why I haven‚Äôt quit; it‚Äôs never been for fame or fortune (as they were not rewarded to skaters when I started), but I‚Äôve had my share of both

We‚Äôve made a lot of progress since last week and we believe we‚Äôll have things repaired later in the week, which will allow us to remain on our regular patch cadence going forward. The League and TFT teams will update you soon on what this means for each game.

7/7

We‚Äôre committed to transparency and will release a full report in the future detailing the attackers‚Äô techniques, the areas where Riot‚Äôs security controls failed, and the steps we‚Äôre taking to ensure this doesn‚Äôt happen again.

6/7

Our security teams and globally recognized external consultants continue to evaluate the attack and audit our systems. We‚Äôve also notified law enforcement and are in active cooperation with them as they investigate the attack and the group behind it.

5/7

The illegally obtained source code also includes a number of experimental features. While we hope some of these game modes and other changes eventually make it out to players, most of this content is in prototype and there‚Äôs no guarantee it will ever be released.

4/7

Truthfully, any exposure of source code can increase the likelihood of new cheats emerging. Since the attack, we‚Äôve been working to assess its impact on anticheat and to be prepared to deploy fixes as quickly as possible if needed.

3/7

Today, we received a ransom email. Needless to say, we won‚Äôt pay.

While this attack disrupted our build environment and could cause issues in the future, most importantly we remain confident that no player data or player personal information was compromised.

2/7

As promised, we wanted to update you on the status of last week‚Äôs cyber attack. Over the weekend, our analysis confirmed source code for League, TFT, and a legacy anticheat platform were exfiltrated by the attackers.

1/7
Please be patient with us as we work through this, and we‚Äôll keep you posted as we continue our investigation.
Unfortunately, this has temporarily affected our ability to release content. While our teams are working hard on a fix, we expect this to impact our upcoming patch cadence across multiple games.

Earlier this week, systems in our development environment were compromised via a social engineering attack. We don‚Äôt have all the answers right now, but we wanted to communicate early and let you know there is no indication that player data or personal information was obtained.

If the Fed does not pivot, the set-up will be more like 1929. The Fed raised rates in 1929 to squelch financial speculation and then, in 1930, Congress passed Smoot-Hawley, putting 50%+ tariffs on more than 20,000 goods and pushing the global economy into the Great Depression.

As inflation dropped to -15% in June 1921, the Fed lowered interest rates from 7% in May 1921 to 4% in July 1922, tripping the switch for the Roaring Twenties. From August 1921 to September 1929, the Dow Jones Industrial Average compounded at a annual rate of 25%.

If inflation drops below the Fed‚Äôs 2% target and economic activity disappoints, then interest rates are likely to surprise on the low side of expectations next year, ushering in this century‚Äôs rendition of the Roaring Twenties.

Founded in 1913 and challenged by its first bout of serious inflation, the Fed raised interest rates less than two-fold from 4.6% to 7% in 1919-1920. Faced with much lower inflation this time around, the Fed has increased interest rates 16-fold, a serious mistake in our view.

During WWI and the Spanish Flu, supply chain and other shocks pushed inflation to 20%+. At its worst in June 1920, inflation peaked at 24% but then dropped precipitously in one year to -15% in June 1921. We would not be surprised to see broad-based inflation turn negative in 2023

Prior to the Roaring Twenties, the world was at war - WWI - and suffering a pandemic - Spanish Flu. While both had a more serious impact on the global economy, today‚Äôs combination is a strong echo that could result in much lower than expected inflation and a boom in innovation.

If inflation is unwinding, as we believe, then we could be heading back to the future, the Roaring Twenties, the last time several general purpose technologies evolved at the same time: telephone, electricity, and the internal combustion engine. The setup is remarkably similar!

through this journey and neither compares to the feeling of riding away from a trick that you‚Äôve battled for hours, weeks or years. I continue to do it because I can still be creative in a way gives me a personal sense of pride and validation.

both physically and emotionally, for being singularly focused on something. I hope that it gives some perspective on why we do this and why I haven‚Äôt quit; it‚Äôs never been for fame or fortune (as they were not rewarded to skaters when I started), but I‚Äôve had my share of both
